    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> April 5610</date>.</p>
			<p>My dear Sir&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">I duly received the<lb/> two parcels containing the <date>Jany</date>. <date>Feby</date><lb/> &#38; <date>March</date> Nos. of the &#8220;Occident&#8221; to&#45;<lb/>&#61;gether with your communications<lb/> accompanying them. I have col&#61;<lb/>&#61;lected the subscriptions and paid<lb/> your draft on me in favor of &#8220;<persName>Miss<lb/> Peixotto</persName>. The <persName>Revd. Mr. Jacob</persName> has<lb/> declined continuing as a subscriber on<lb/> the plea &#8220;that the Occident was of<lb/> &#8220;no use to him.&#8221; I have however<lb/> to request that you will still send<lb/> over the same quantity having<lb/> procured another subscriber &#40;<persName>Mr. J M<lb/> Lawrence</persName>&#41; who also requiring the 5th<lb/> 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> &#38; 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> volumes <hi rend="underline">Bound</hi>. Be good<lb/> enough to let me know the cost<lb/> thereof.</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">You are aware of <persName>Mr. Nathans</persName><lb/> appointment as <add>Hebrew</add> of <placeName>New Orleans</placeName></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>for which city he will leave on<lb/> <date>Sunday Evening the 21<hi rend="sup">st</hi></date> in the &#8220;Great<lb/> Western&#8221; via <placeName><sic>Havanna</sic></placeName>. I have<lb/> resigned the mastership of the<lb/> Hebrew National Institution&#44; and<lb/> taken the Academy of <persName>Mr. N</persName> who<lb/> has kindly handed it over to me<lb/> since the <date>1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> April</date>. In consequence<lb/> of this step&#44; I must&#44; &#40;for the present<lb/> at least&#41;&#8212;abandon the idea of<lb/> quitting <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>. Notwithstanding&#44;&#8212;<lb/> my sincere thanks are due to you<lb/> for the kind attention you have<lb/> shown in furnishing me with<lb/> confirmation and advice&#44; relative to<lb/> ministerial situations in the <placeName>U. S.</placeName><lb/> I have devoted my entire attention<lb/> to the Portuguese Minhag&#44; and&#44; without<lb/> vanity I have profited so well by<lb/> <persName>Hasan Lopez&#39;s</persName> tuition<add>&#63;</add> that no one<lb/> would believe that I had been<lb/> attached to a German Congregation. Of<lb/> course&#44; I officiate as a Portuguese Hazan<lb/> in <placeName>Spanish Town</placeName>&#44; from which congregation<lb/> I have received several addresses &#38;</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>testimonials&#44; <add>&#63;</add> <hi rend="underline">two</hi> from the<lb/> Director of the Hebrew National Insti&#61;<lb/>&#61;tution since my resignation.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Synagogue affairs in <placeName>Jamaica</placeName><lb/>&#8212;I regret to state&#8212;are not in a<lb/> flourishing condition. There seems<lb/> to be a feeling rising in <placeName>Falmouth</placeName><lb/> to establish a synagogue there. The<lb/> Jewish Community in that town numbers<lb/> about Seventy Souls who are&#44; with<lb/> scarcely an exception&#44; in good circum&#61;<lb/>&#61;stances. Perhaps you will lend your<lb/> pen towards stimulating them in the<lb/> &#8220;good <sic>cauce</sic>.&#8221;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">The administration for the<lb/> &#8220;School&#8221; lately elected is</p>
			<list type="simple">
			<head></head>
			  <item rend="indent(2)"><persName>P Laurence</persName>&#160;&#160;&#160;President</item>
			  <item rend="indent(2)"><persName>G Delgado</persName>&#160;&#160;&#160;Vice</item>
			  <item rend="indent(2)"><persName>Alex Aria</persName>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Treas.</item>
			</list>
			<p></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">The number of Directors not being<lb/> yet complete&#44; I am unable to send<lb/> you a perfect list. I will however<lb/> do so at a future period &#40;Dr.&#41;</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)">With best wishes.</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)">Believe me</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)">Yours Very Truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Henry S. Jacobs</persName>.</p>
          
        </body>
